{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "car-rental-api-collection",
		"name": "Car Rental API",
		"description": "API collection for the Car Rental project. Import this file in Postman to test all endpoints.\n\n## Authentication (when you need a token)\n\n| Endpoint pattern | `Authorization: Bearer <token>` |\n| --- | --- |\n| `POST /api/login` | **Not used** — public. Response includes `data.token`; Postman saves it to `{{token}}`. |\n| `POST /api/v1/users` (register) | **Not used** — public, but the server may return **403** if registration is disabled (`allow_user_registration`). |\n| `GET /api/user`, `POST /api/logout` | **Required** — Sanctum. |\n| All other `/api/v1/...` routes | **Required** — same Bearer token as above. |\n\nThis collection sets **Bearer Token** auth at the collection level (`{{token}}`). Requests that must be public override auth to **No Auth** (Login, Register User).\n\n## Setup\n1. Set `base_url` (default: `http://localhost` — add port if needed, e.g. `http://localhost:8000`).\n2. Run **Login**; token is stored automatically.\n3. Fill path variables from responses: `car_id`, `driver_id`, `customer_id`, `transaction_id`, `booking_id`, `car_import_id`, `driver_import_id` (UUIDs).\n\n## Optional query keys (frontend reference)\nMany `GET` endpoints accept optional keys documented on each request: pagination (`per_page`), nested `filter[...]`, `sort`, `include`, date ranges, etc. If a key is omitted, the API uses defaults described on that request.\n\n**User registration:** `POST /api/v1/users` needs `name`, `email`, `password`, `password_confirmation` — no Bearer; may still fail with 403 when registration is off.\n\n**CSV imports:** `multipart/form-data` with field `file`; then poll import status by ID.\n\n**Transactions:** create/update bodies require `name` (max 255) where applicable. Bookings list: newest first (`created_at`, then `start_date`).",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "base_url",
			"value": "http://localhost"
		},
		{
			"key": "token",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "car_id",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "driver_id",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "customer_id",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "transaction_id",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "booking_id",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "car_import_id",
			"value": ""
		},
		{
			"key": "driver_import_id",
			"value": ""
		}
	],
	"auth": {
		"type": "bearer",
		"bearer": [
			{
				"key": "token",
				"value": "{{token}}",
				"type": "string"
			}
		]
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Auth",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Login",
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "noauth"
						},
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "login"]
						},
						"description": "Public endpoint — **do not** send `Authorization`. Send JSON `email` and `password`. On success, use `data.token` as `Bearer` for all `/api/v1/*` routes (except register). Postman saves `token` automatically."
					},
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const json = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (json.data && json.data.token) {",
									"        pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.data.token);",
									"    }",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Logout",
					"request": {
						"description": "**Bearer required.** Revokes the current Sanctum token. After this, set a new token via Login.",
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/logout",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "logout"]
						}
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Current User",
					"request": {
						"description": "**Bearer required.** Returns the authenticated user for the current token.",
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "user"]
						}
					}
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "Users",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Register User",
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "noauth"
						},
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Jane Smith\",\n    \"email\": \"jane@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password\",\n    \"password_confirmation\": \"password\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/users",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "users"]
						},
						"description": "Register a new user account. **No Bearer token** — this route is public. Body: `name`, `email`, `password`, `password_confirmation`. Returns **403** when registration is disabled server-side (`allow_user_registration`). When enabled, returns success without needing any API key beyond optional rate limits."
					}
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "Cars",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Add Car",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"make\": \"Toyota\",\n    \"model\": \"Camry\",\n    \"plate_number\": \"ABC-1234\",\n    \"mileage\": 50000,\n    \"type\": \"sedan\",\n    \"number_of_seats\": 5,\n    \"year\": 2022\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/cars",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "cars"]
						}
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "Import Cars CSV",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "formdata",
							"formdata": [
								{
									"key": "file",
									"type": "file",
									"src": ""
								}
							]
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/cars/import",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "cars", "import"]
						},
						"description": "Queue a CSV import of cars (multipart/form-data, `file` required)."
					},
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 202) {",
									"    const json = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (json.data && json.data.id) {",
									"        pm.collectionVariables.set('car_import_id', json.data.id);",
									"    }",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Car Import Status",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/cars/imports/{{car_import_id}}",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "cars", "imports", "{{car_import_id}}"]
						},
						"description": "Fetch status/result summary for a queued car import job."
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "List Cars",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/cars?per_page=15&make=Toyota&model=Camry&type=sedan&number_of_seats=5",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "cars"],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "per_page",
									"value": "15",
									"description": "Optional. 1–100, default 15."
								},
								{
									"key": "make",
									"value": "Toyota",
									"description": "Optional. Filter by make (string)."
								},
								{
									"key": "model",
									"value": "Camry",
									"description": "Optional. Filter by model (string)."
								},
								{
									"key": "type",
									"value": "sedan",
									"description": "Optional. Filter by vehicle type (string)."
								},
								{
									"key": "number_of_seats",
									"value": "5",
									"description": "Optional. Integer minimum 1."
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "**Bearer required.** Lists available cars. All query keys are optional; omit them to list with defaults."
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Single Car",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/cars/{{car_id}}",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "cars", "{{car_id}}"]
						}
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "Update Car",
					"request": {
						"method": "PUT",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"make\": \"Toyota\",\n    \"model\": \"Camry\",\n    \"plate_number\": \"ABC-1234\",\n    \"mileage\": 55000,\n    \"type\": \"sedan\",\n    \"number_of_seats\": 5,\n    \"year\": 2022\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/cars/{{car_id}}",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "cars", "{{car_id}}"]
						}
					}
				}
			]
		},
